"John G. Guilbault, age 65, of Point Avenue, Warwick, died at home on December 29, 2012.\n\nBorn in Providence, the son of Margaret (McDaid) Guilbault of Warwick, and the late George A. Guilbault, he lived inWarwick for over 30 years. Mr. Guilbault was a plater at Unique Plating in Johnston before retiring in 2002.\n\nBesides his mother, he is survived by a sister, Margaret I. Gervais of Warwick; and two nephews, Raymond S. Gervais and his wife, Melissa and daughter Angelica, of California, and Robert J. Gervais of Warwick.\n\nHis funeral service will be held on Wednesday, January 9, at 11 a.m. in the Barrett & Cotter Funeral Home, 1328 Warwick Avenue, Spring Green, Warwick. Relatives and friends are invited, and may visit at the funeral home on Wednesday from 10 \u2013 11 a.m. Burial will be private."
