"\u201cIn every block of marble I see a statue as plain as though it stood before me, shaped and perfect in attitude and action. I have only to hew away the rough walls that imprison the lovely apparition to reveal it to the other eyes as mine see it.\u201d ~ Michelangelo Buonarroti\n\nLike this:\n\nAt first glance, you may think this elegantly sophisticated home hails from Paris or London but surprisingly it is located on Worth Avenue in Palm Beach! Swedish designer Lars Bolander and his wife Nadine brilliantly re-imagined three dilapidated apartments into a 12 room penthouse with a glorious rooftop terrace\u2026the drawing room (above) is thoughtfully decorated with a large French painting that presides over an 18th century French console table topped with Italian iron lamps\u2026gorgeous! I love that amid all the precious art and antiques, this home remains approachable, warm and inviting\u2026a perfect blend of country comfort and European chic\u2026enjoy!"
