"Luxury Vegan Shoe Company Debuts Affordable Line\n\nCruelty-free shoe makers Beyond Skin offered vintage-inspired luxury footwear for more than a decade, but has now launched a Kickstarter campaign to raise funds for a new collection of affordable heels, boots, and loafers, dubbed its Diffusion line. The company recently faced financial hardship and its manufacturing factory was closed down. The designers Natalie Dean and Heather Whittle hope Kickstarter will aid with funding for production. The 10 new designs are crafted from Italian leather alternatives and are completely vegan. There are 11 days left in the campaign with a goal of 20,000 British pounds set."
"Cantonment\n\nCantonment was the rebirth of [U-D-R]. Anthony was serving his last year in the army in Korea, with some encouragement from family and friends (and a fellow industrial musician he met there), he began work on reviving the band. There was no real way to record vocals with the equipment he had with him, so he took the best of the [U-D-R] songs that were available to him and rewrote all of the music and tried to improve on the vocals as much as possible.\n\nThe album finalized in the spring of 2011 and released commercially on the 7th of June, 2011."
