"Runge enters not guilty plea\n\nDuPage to try 2 of 7 murder cases\n\nPaul Runge, charged in the deaths of 7 women, pleaded not guilty Monday in DuPage County Circuit Court to the murder of two Hanover Park sisters.\n\nHe is expected to plead not guilty to the murder of four women and a girl in Cook County when he appears in court there Friday.\n\nRunge, 31, wearing shackles on his arms and legs and with extra security personnel present, answered procedural questions from DuPage Judge Mark Dwyer. He has been accused of a killing spree that allegedly began in 1995 with the sexual assault, murder and dismemberment of a 25-year-old Streamwood woman.\n\nLater that year, he is alleged to have killed the two Hanover Park sisters, Dzeneta and Amela Pasanbegovic. In an 18-count indictment returned by the DuPage grand jury, he is accused of attacking and killing them after luring them to his Glendale Heights home with promises of a house-cleaning job. Their bodies have never been recovered.\n\nThe two women, who immigrated to the U.S. from war-torn Bosnia in January 1995, were living with an uncle in Hanover Park.\n\nRunge also is accused of killing four women and"
