"Peacefully, with family by her side at University Hospital, London, on Sunday, September 17th, 2017, in her 86th year. Elva, of Owen Sound and formerly of Paisley. Loving Mother of Patricia and her husband Lorne Noseworthy, Barbara Nelson and her partner Rick, Bob and his wife Linda, Linda and her husband Jason Payne, and Terri and her husband Chris Rau. Proud Grandma of Shawn (Jaime), Tim, Shauna, Jenn (Will), Kyle, Kiefer, and Hunter. Great grandma of Jaelyn, Adara, Brexton, Sophie, Quinn, and Tony. Predeceased by her brother Alex McEachnie.\n\nFriends will be received on Tuesday, September 19th, 2017 from 7-9pm at the Tannahill Funeral Home, 1178 4th Ave West, Owen Sound, 519-376-3710. A funeral service will be held in the chapel on Wednesday, September 20th, 2017 at 11:00am. Interment Paisley Cemetery.\n\nMemorial donations to the Chesley & District Health Services Foundation would be appreciated by the family."
