"Privates on Parade\n\nTime Out says\n\n4 out of 5 stars\n\nDetails\n\nTime Out says\n\n4 out of 5 stars\n\nActor Sophiya Haque passed away in January 2013, during the play's run. RIP.\n\nLike 'Apocalypse Now' given the Kenneth Williams remix or 'Cabaret' retold by No\u00ebl Coward, Peter Nichols's determinedly camp 1977 war satire is an absurd and slightly flimsy beast, teetering precariously between being deceptively lightweight and genuinely so. It is also incredibly good fun, and a canny choice for former Donmar Warehouse boss Michael Grandage to begin his five play, 18-month stand in the West End with, an assurance that the heavyweight director is, above all, here to entertain.\n\nAs are the protagonists of Nichols's innuendo-laden comedy, which follows the misadventures of a fictional song and dance unit of the British army in post-war Singapore. At the head of them is the queenly acting captain Terri Dennis, played with almost mystical flamboyancy by Simon Russell Beale.\n\nLike an even gayer version of 'Cabaret's Emcee, Terri seems to almost exist apart from the play's events, materialising every now and again \u2013 generally in drag \u2013 to either comment on the action or sing some ribald number for the lads."
"The 17 Most Ridiculous Outfits At The MTV Europe Music Awards\n\nMiley Cyrus caused controversy when she lit a joint during her EMA acceptance speech. But you should see what she was wearing!REUTERS/Remko De Waal\n\nYou thought this year's MTV Video Music Awards show in Brooklyn was a twerk-filled controversy?\n\nThe network's Europe Music Awards took things to a whole new level last night in Amsterdam as Miley Cyrus smoked a joint onstage, Iggy Azaelia had a serious wardrobe malfunction, and musicians wore some of the most ridiculous outfits we have ever seen.\n\nCheck out the craziest costumes \u2014 because they can only be called that \u2014 from Sunday night's 20th MTV Europe Music Awards at the Ziggo Dome.\n\nMiley Cyrus continued to push the limits in this barely-there dress covered in Biggie Smalls and Tupac Shakur's faces.\n\nJoel Ryan/Invision/AP\n\nWhile accepting her first-ever EMA in the Best Video category for \u201cWrecking Ball,\u201d Cyrus lit up a joint while wearing this unexplainable leotard and fur shrug.\n\nIan Gavan/Getty\n\nEllie Goulding left little to the imagination on the red carpet before she presented during the show.\n\nJoel Ryan/Invision/AP\n\nKaty Perry rocked a similar black see-through number after the show.\n\nJoel Ryan/Invision/AP"
"Petrol Additives\n\nPetrol additives are a great way to ensure that your vehicle is well-maintained in places you can't reach. A petrol additive can clean the multiple valves and carburettor, and fuel additives such as Wynn's even restore overall engine performance.\n\nA good fuel treatment can help to reduce carbon emissions and avoids further trouble when trying to start if your vehicle is sometimes problematic. A cheap petrol treatment may harm the catalytic converters, but everything we sell has been checked and approved by the appropriate authorities.\n\nAll you need to do is follow the instructions on the back of each product for the required amount to add. Some only need around 500mls that will cover 50 litres of petrol for around 6000 miles- it's definitely worth the small price tag if it's something you're considering.\n\nCookie Use\n\nWe use cookies to improve your experience on our website. Continuing to use this site indicates that you agree to our use of cookies. For more details about cookies and how to manage them, see our Privacy & Cookies page."
