"Best 2013 Christmas markets in Europe\n\n19/12/2013\n\nblogo\n\nChristmas markets are an ancient tradition originally from Northen Europe.\nNowadays diffused across all countries and regions, Christmas markets are generally held outdoors, in the town centres, and provide great opportunity for a taste of local culinary traditions and festive celebration.\n\nIf you are in Nice, the place for Christmas celebrations is Place Mass\u00e9na's market, open everyday from 11 am to 8pm, or until 9pm on Friday and Saturdays, until 1\u00b0 January 2014. Here, over 60 stands offer a range of Christmas products form the French RivieraPlace Mass\u00e9na is probably the most beautiful square in Nice, at the heart of its shopping district and of the city night life. The square has just come back to its usual splendor after undergoing years of refurbishment, so it's definetily woth a visit this Christmas.\n\nIf you are heading to Praga, make sure you visit the city's best loved market in Staromestsk\u00e9 namesti (Old Town Square), which also covers the nearby Vaclav namesti, orWenceslas Square. The charm of the latter location, with its Gothic, Baroque and Renaissance architecture, is magnifically amplified by the Christmas decoration.\n\nThe market here is made up of 150 wooden huts"
"PHILADELPHIA \u2013 It was probably the biggest upset of the lockout \u2013 the Baltimore-based Big 3 of Carmelo Anthony, LeBron James and Chris Paul losing to Team Philly on Sunday night, 131-122, at the sweaty jam-packed Palestra.\n\nBefore a rowdy crowd of 8,000 fans, the Philly Big 3 of Tyreke Evans (Pennsylvania native), Louis Williams (76ers) and Hakim Warrick (Philadelphia native) took out Team Melo, hanging on after taking a 16-point lead in the first half.\n\nWarrick, in particular, abused Anthony in the first half with an array of athletic fastbreak dunks. Team Melo wasn\u2019t exactly getting back on D.\n\n\u201cThat\u2019s why I got these guys, I knew they\u2019d come out here and get this win,\u2019\u2019 Warrick said. \u201cI know the type of competitors LeBron and \u2019Melo are and I knew it was going to be no love affair. I had to make sure I had some shoulders with me. I know nobody gave us a chance but I knew we had too much heart in this locker room.\u2019\u2019\n\nThey sweated buckets, though, as did the spectators. You could have lost 10 pounds in the sauna that was the no-air-conditioned barn on the University of Pennsylvania campus. Anthony and James"
