"Kevin Windham and Carmichael are the only riders to win both classes at Unadilla.\n\nIn 2005, Suzuki\u2019s Ricky Carmichael and Broc Hepler swept both classes at Unadilla. Prior to that year, Suzuki had not swept an AMA Motocross event since May 10, 1981, in Atlanta, when Kent Howerton and Mark Barnett took top honors.\n\nIn 1996, Greg Albertyn snapped a 15 year, 124-round winless drought for Suzuki when he won at Unadilla.\n\nIn 2003 at Unadilla, Windham put a stop to Carmichael\u2019s 18-race win streak by winning both motos en route to the overall victory.\n\nFor the first time since 2000, a rider other than Ricky Carmichael will win Round 6 of AMA Motocross.\n\nThere have been three brand sweeps at Unadilla (when a brand wins both classes): Suzuki (Carmichael and Hepler) in 2005; and Kawasaki (Mike Kiedrowski and James Dobb) in 1993 and (Mike LaRocco and Ryan Hughes) in 1994.\n\nAMA Motocross Lites Stats:\n\nFirst race, October 15, 1989, with Damon Bradshaw winning on a Yamaha.\n\nThis will be the 18th time the gate will drop for an AMA Motocross Lites race at Unadilla.\n\nFirst time winners at Unadilla: Broc Hepler \u2014 Suzuki (2005) and James Dobb \u2014 Kawasaki"
